\title{Torsion Submodule}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-19}
\taxon{definition}

\p{Let #{R} be a ring, let #{M} be an #{R}-module. The \define{Torsion Submodule} #{\Tor(M)} consists of all [[ra-003O]]s of #{M}.}

\p{When #{R} is commutative, this is actually an #{R}-module.}

\p{When #{R} is noncommutative, we need some additional properties imposed on #{R} for #{\Tor(M)} to be a right #{R}-module.}